{
  "id": "feature-perf-008-api-caching-dedup",
  "title": "HTTP API Client Caching, Request Deduplication, and Retry Logic",
  "category": "Performance",
  "description": "## Problem\nThe HTTP API client (`apps/ui/src/lib/http-api-client.ts`) has NO response caching, NO request deduplication, and NO retry logic. Every API call hits the server fresh. Multiple components fetching the same data simultaneously each make separate requests. This causes excessive network traffic, unnecessary server load, and slower perceived performance.\n\n## Current Behavior\n\n### No Response Caching (line 878):\n```typescript\nprivate async get<T>(endpoint: string): Promise<T> {\n  await waitForApiKeyInit();\n  const response = await fetch(`${this.serverUrl}${endpoint}`, {\n    headers: this.getHeaders(),\n    credentials: 'include',\n    cache: NO_STORE_CACHE_MODE,  // Explicitly DISABLES browser caching!\n  });\n  // Direct response.json() return, no caching\n}\n```\n\n### No Request Deduplication:\nMultiple components calling the same endpoint concurrently each make separate requests. For example:\n- `use-board-features.ts` fetches all features for board view\n- `use-running-agents.ts` fetches all features from ALL projects to count running agents\n- Both can be active on the same page, fetching identical data\n\n### No Retry Logic:\nRequests fail immediately on error (lines 856-867, 886-897). Only specific places like `login-view.tsx` implement manual retry.\n\n### No SWR/React Query:\nThe project does NOT use SWR or React Query. All data fetching is manual with useCallback/useEffect.\n\n## Required Changes\n1. Add an in-memory response cache layer to `HttpApiClient` with configurable TTL per endpoint category:\n   - Features list: 5-10s TTL (frequently polled)\n   - Settings: 60s TTL (rarely changes)\n   - Models list: 300s TTL (almost never changes)\n   - Health check: no cache\n2. Add request deduplication: if the same GET request is in-flight, return the existing Promise\n3. Add configurable retry with exponential backoff for transient failures (network errors, 502/503)\n4. Add `staleWhileRevalidate` option: return cached data immediately while refreshing in background\n5. Add a `cache.invalidate(pattern)` method for targeted cache busting after mutations\n6. Expose a `forceRefresh` option for when fresh data is explicitly needed\n\n## Pattern to Follow\n```typescript\nclass RequestCache {\n  private cache = new Map<string, { data: unknown; timestamp: number; ttl: number }>();\n  private inflight = new Map<string, Promise<unknown>>();\n\n  async get<T>(key: string, fetcher: () => Promise<T>, options: { ttl: number; swr?: boolean }): Promise<T> {\n    // 1. Check inflight - deduplicate\n    const existing = this.inflight.get(key);\n    if (existing) return existing as Promise<T>;\n\n    // 2. Check cache\n    const cached = this.cache.get(key);\n    if (cached && Date.now() - cached.timestamp < cached.ttl) {\n      return cached.data as T;\n    }\n\n    // 3. Fetch and cache\n    const promise = fetcher().then(data => {\n      this.cache.set(key, { data, timestamp: Date.now(), ttl: options.ttl });\n      this.inflight.delete(key);\n      return data;\n    });\n    this.inflight.set(key, promise);\n\n    // 4. SWR: return stale while revalidating\n    if (options.swr && cached) {\n      promise.catch(() => {}); // Background refresh\n      return cached.data as T;\n    }\n    return promise;\n  }\n\n  invalidate(pattern?: string) { ... }\n}\n```\n\n## Files to Modify\n- `apps/ui/src/lib/http-api-client.ts` - Add caching layer, request dedup, retry logic\n- `apps/ui/src/hooks/use-running-agents.ts` - Use cached features endpoint instead of full re-fetch\n- `apps/ui/src/components/views/board-view/hooks/use-board-features.ts` - Leverage cache, change event handlers from full re-fetch to cache invalidation + re-fetch\n- `apps/ui/src/hooks/use-usage-tracking.ts` - Use cached API calls\n\n## Expected Impact\n- 40-60% reduction in API requests during normal board usage\n- Faster perceived load times (stale-while-revalidate)\n- Reduced server CPU and I/O load\n- Graceful handling of transient network failures\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- Network tab shows deduplicated requests (no concurrent identical GETs)\n- Cached responses returned instantly for repeat requests within TTL\n- SWR mode shows stale data immediately while refreshing in background\n- Cache invalidates correctly after mutations (create/update/delete feature)\n- Retry logic recovers from transient 502/503 errors\n- No stale data visible after mutations (cache properly invalidated)\n\n## Reference\n- `apps/server/src/services/codex-model-cache-service.ts` - Good example of TTL caching with request deduplication",
